{{Orphan|date=September 2018}}
In mathematics, the '''continuous ''q''-Legendre polynomials''' are a family of basic hypergeometric [[orthogonal polynomials]] in the basic [[Askey scheme]]. {{harvtxt|Koekoek|Lesky|Swarttouw|2010}} give a detailed list of their properties.<ref>{{citation | last1 = Koekoek | first1 = Roelof | last2 = Lesky | first2 = Peter A. | last3 = Swarttouw | first3 = René F. | doi = 10.1007/978-3-642-05014-5 | isbn = 978-3-642-05013-8 | mr = 2656096 | page = 14 | publisher = Springer-Verlag | location = Berlin | series = Springer Monographs in Mathematics | title = Hypergeometric orthogonal polynomials and their ''q''-analogues | year = 2010}}</ref>
