{{primary sources|date=September 2013}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = <!--Uses page name if omitted--> | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | status = Active<!-- e.g. defunct, active, inactive ... --> | genre = [[Mathematics]] conference | frequency = Quadrennial | location = | country = | years_active = | first = {{start date and age|1992}} | founder_name = | last = | prev = 2016 ([[Berlin]]) | next = 2020 ([[Slovenia]]) | participants = | attendance = | area = | budget = | activity = | patron = | organised = <!--"organized=" also works--> | filing = <!-- Filing status --> | people = | member = | website = {{URL|https://www.8ecm.si/|ECM 8}} | footnotes = }}
The '''European Congress of Mathematics''' ('''ECM''') is an international congress of the [[mathematics]] community, held every four years. Its objectives are "to present various new aspects of pure and applied mathematics to a wide audience, to be a forum for discussion of the relationship between mathematics and society in Europe, and to enhance cooperation among mathematicians from all European countries."
The Congress is held under the auspices of the [[European Mathematical Society]] (EMS), and was one of its earliest initiatives. The [[European_Mathematical_Society#Prizes|EMS Prizes]] are awarded at the beginning of the Congress.
== List of congresses ==
* 1992 &ndash; [[Paris]] * 1996 &ndash; [[Budapest]] * 2000 &ndash; [[Barcelona]] * 2004 &ndash; [[Stockholm]] * 2008 &ndash; [[Amsterdam]] * 2012 &ndash; [[Kraków]] * 2016 &ndash; [[Berlin]]
The 8th European Congress of Mathematics will be held in [[Slovenia]] in 2020.
==External links== * [http://www.8ecm.si ECM 2020] * [http://www.7ecm.de ECM 2016] * [http://www.6ecm.pl ECM 2012] * [http://www.5ecm.nl ECM 2008] * [http://www.math.kth.se/4ecm/ ECM 2004] * [http://www.emis.de/ECM.html EMIS on ECM]
